{
  "children": [
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "üíº Fee Estimate Calculator"
        }
      ],
      "type": "h1"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "In order to properly calculate client fees, consulting projects often require you to make plans for your staff allocation, costs and target rates. Let's run through an example of how this looks like in Decipad:"
        }
      ],
      "type": "p"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Staff Allocation"
        }
      ],
      "type": "h2"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Target staff allocation for the project:"
        }
      ],
      "type": "p"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ],
      "type": "table-input",
      "tableData": {
        "variableName": "Allocation",
        "columns": [
          {
            "columnName": "Staff",
            "cells": [
              "Director",
              "Manager",
              "Senior Consultant",
              "Consultant 1",
              "Consultant 2"
            ],
            "cellType": "string"
          },
          {
            "columnName": "Month1",
            "cellType": "number",
            "cells": ["16", "100", "120", "160", "160"]
          },
          {
            "columnName": "Month2",
            "cellType": "number",
            "cells": ["8", "60", "100", "160", "160"]
          },
          {
            "columnName": "Month3",
            "cellType": "number",
            "cells": ["18", "80", "120", "160", "160"]
          },
          {
            "columnName": "Month4",
            "cellType": "number",
            "cells": ["16", "120", "160", "160", "160"]
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ],
      "type": "p"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Rates and Costs"
        }
      ],
      "type": "h2"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Target rates and direct costs associated with each staff member:"
        }
      ],
      "type": "p"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Financials = { "
            }
          ],
          "type": "code_line"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "  ...Allocation"
            }
          ],
          "type": "code_line"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "  TargetRate = [350 ‚Ç¨/hour, 239, 144, 102, 102]"
            }
          ],
          "type": "code_line"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "  DirectCost = [148 ‚Ç¨/hour, 110, 65, 41, 41]\n}"
            }
          ],
          "type": "code_line"
        }
      ],
      "type": "code_block"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ],
      "type": "p",
      "id": "__PE_pvZc96VLz-3YvFVq"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Note: There are still some limitations with tables and therefore we couldn't reuse the Staff dimension to quickly breakdown target rates and direct costs through existing staff members. The table above had therefore to be created manually using the Decipad language in a calculations block, but soon you'll be able to do it directly in the table's interface ‚ú®"
        }
      ],
      "type": "blockquote"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ],
      "type": "p"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Project Gross Value"
        }
      ],
      "type": "h2",
      "id": "J5Az3wnkJuhiA2lWuuJU3"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "By multiplying the "
        },
        {
          "text": "target rates ",
          "bold": true
        },
        {
          "text": "by each staff monthly "
        },
        {
          "text": "allocation ",
          "bold": true
        },
        {
          "text": "we can calculate the total gross value of the project:"
        }
      ],
      "type": "p"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "GrossValue = sum((Financials.TargetRate) * ((Allocation.Month1 + Allocation.Month2 + Allocation.Month3 + Allocation.Month4) in hours))"
            }
          ],
          "type": "code_line"
        }
      ],
      "type": "code_block"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Project Expenses"
        }
      ],
      "type": "h2"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Based on previous projects, we're going to assume that "
        },
        {
          "text": "general expenses",
          "bold": true
        },
        {
          "text": " correspond to 1% of the project's gross value:"
        }
      ],
      "type": "p"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "GeneralExpenses = GrossValue * 1%"
            }
          ],
          "type": "code_line"
        }
      ],
      "type": "code_block"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Direct costs",
          "bold": true
        },
        {
          "text": " can be easily derived by multiplying each staff hourly direct cost by their hourly project allocation:"
        }
      ],
      "type": "p"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "DirectCosts = sum((Financials.DirectCost) * ((Allocation.Month1 + Allocation.Month2 + Allocation.Month3 + Allocation.Month4) in hours))"
            }
          ],
          "type": "code_line"
        }
      ],
      "type": "code_block"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Fee Estimate"
        }
      ],
      "type": "h2"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Imagine that it has been established internally that when negotiating the value of the project with clients we shouldn't "
        },
        {
          "text": "discount",
          "bold": true
        },
        {
          "text": " our hourly rates more than "
        },
        {
          "text": "25%",
          "bold": true
        },
        {
          "text": "."
        }
      ],
      "type": "p",
      "id": "KFACGXRrNw2qvrkLD47Mq"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Let's consider a few "
        },
        {
          "text": "scenarios",
          "bold": true
        },
        {
          "text": " for this exercise then:"
        }
      ],
      "type": "p"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ],
      "type": "table-input",
      "tableData": {
        "variableName": "Discount",
        "columns": [
          {
            "columnName": "Scenario",
            "cells": ["Max Discount", "Avg Discount", "No Discount"],
            "cellType": "string"
          },
          {
            "columnName": "Value",
            "cellType": "number",
            "cells": [".25", ".16", "0"]
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ],
      "type": "p"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "We can take these scenarios to calculate our "
        },
        {
          "text": "target project fee ",
          "bold": true
        },
        {
          "text": "and resulting "
        },
        {
          "text": "gross margin",
          "bold": true
        },
        {
          "text": " (the table's interface does not yet allow us to add calculated columns, so we will have to do it through a calculations block):"
        }
      ],
      "type": "p"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "ProjectFinancials = {"
            }
          ],
          "type": "code_line"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "  Scenario = Discount.Scenario\n  ProjectFee = GrossValue * (1 - Discount.Value)"
            }
          ],
          "type": "code_line",
          "id": "si8Y6wg5tt81aEm_4U3_e"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "  GrossMargin = ProjectFee - DirectCosts - GeneralExpenses"
            }
          ],
          "type": "code_line"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "  GrossMarginPercentage = round((ProjectFee - DirectCosts - GeneralExpenses) / ProjectFee, 2)"
            }
          ],
          "type": "code_line"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "}"
            }
          ],
          "type": "code_line",
          "id": "si8Y6wg5tt81aEm_4U3_e"
        }
      ],
      "type": "code_block"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ],
      "type": "p"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "If by any chance you want to add a new scenario based on your negotiations with your client, you can quickly do it by just adding a new scenario to the discount table. And you also don't need to worry about updating every calculation that references that table because everything is already synchronized. Nice huh? üôÇ"
        }
      ],
      "type": "p"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ],
      "type": "p"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "If you liked this model, help us make it even better and share your thoughts and ideas with us on Discord üëê"
        }
      ],
      "type": "p"
    },
    {
      "children": [
